.TH mtui-mcp 1  "mtui-mcp 26.1.0" 
.SH NAME
mtui\-mcp \- MCP server for mtui (tools synthesised from the command registry)
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmtui\-mcp\fR [\fB\-t\fR|\fB\-\-template\-dir\fR] [\fB\-w\fR|\fB\-\-connection\-timeout\fR] [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-debug\fR] [\fB\-c\fR|\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-g\fR|\fB\-\-gitea\-token\fR] [\fB\-\-ssl\-verify\fR] [\fB\-\-transport\fR] [\fB\-\-host\fR] [\fB\-\-port\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
MCP server for mtui (tools synthesised from the command registry)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-t\fR, \fB\-\-template\-dir\fR \fI<DIR>\fR
Override config `mtui.template_dir`
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-connection\-timeout\fR \fI<SECONDS>\fR
Override config `mtui.connection_timeout` (seconds)
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-debug\fR
Enable debugging output
.TP
\fB\-c\fR, \fB\-\-config\fR \fI<FILE>\fR
Override the default config path
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR \fI<COLOR>\fR [default: auto]
Control coloured (log) output. Logs go to stderr; stdout is the transport
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto: Colour iff stderr is a TTY and `NO_COLOR` is unset. The default
.IP \(bu 2
always: Always emit colour escapes
.IP \(bu 2
never: Never emit colour escapes
.RE
.TP
\fB\-g\fR, \fB\-\-gitea\-token\fR \fI<TOKEN>\fR
Gitea access token
.TP
\fB\-\-ssl\-verify\fR \fI<BOOL|PATH>\fR
Override config `mtui.ssl_verify`: TLS certificate verification for all outbound HTTP. Accepts `true`/`false` (and the spellings `yes`/`no`/ `on`/`off`/`1`/`0`), or a path to a custom CA bundle/certificate
.TP
\fB\-\-transport\fR \fI<TRANSPORT>\fR [default: stdio]
MCP transport to serve on: `stdio` (default, one client) or `http` (streamable HTTP, per\-client session isolation)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
stdio: Serve over stdin/stdout (default). One process serves one client
.IP \(bu 2
http: Serve over streamable HTTP. One process serves many isolated clients
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-host\fR \fI<ADDR>\fR [default: 127.0.0.1]
Bind address for `\-\-transport http` (default: 127.0.0.1). Ignored under stdio. Loopback only — rmcp\*(Aqs DNS\-rebinding guard rejects non\-loopback hosts
.TP
\fB\-\-port\fR \fI<PORT>\fR [default: 8000]
Bind port for `\-\-transport http` (default: 8000). Ignored under stdio
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH VERSION
v26.1.0
